  Source:
    Title: Young India
    Editor: M. K. Gandhi
    Locus:
      Date: 15 December 1927
---
As food is necessary for the body, prayer is necessary for the soul. A man
may be able to do without food, for a number of days -- as MacSwiney did
for over seventy days -- but, believing in God, man cannot, should not,
live a moment without prayer.
